    • Constructor Detail

      • Configuration

        public Configuration​(Characteristic[][] characteristics,
                     org.jxmapviewer.viewer.GeoPosition mapOrigin,
                     java.util.LinkedHashSet<org.jxmapviewer.viewer.GeoPosition> wayPoints)
        A constructor generating a new environment with a given map with characteristics.
        Parameters:
        mapOrigin - coordinates of the point [0,0] on the map.
        characteristics - The map with the characteristics of the current environment.
        wayPoints - The WayPoints of the environment.
        Post:
        Sets the max x-coordinate to the x size of the map if the map is valid., Sets the max y-coordinate to the y size of the map if the map is valid., Sets the characteristics to the given map if the map is valid., Sets the max x-coordinate to 0 if the map is not valid., Sets the max y-coordinate to 0 if the map is not valid., Sets the characteristics to an empty list if the map is not valid.
